Just finished highest ever sales for the third year in a row. Dropped 60 lbs, increased the team size, spent more on advertising than ever before, flights….a lot of flights.

Content…a lot of content. A lot of follow up.

Super excited for 2023. The future is always bright and wide open.

Personal insight: Why is surfing so important to me?

Firstly its a way to disconnect from everything and put my attention completely on something else. It moves the needle when I need it to, and reframes my position relative to my business and everything in my life. I never understood the importance of that until I really saw the power of it.

Secondly its challenging. I couldn’t think of something more challenging on multiple fronts for me.  I used to rock climb in the desert and loved that challenge, but surfing is something really difficult to describe unless you try it. It pushes you to face your fears. To look at a 300 foot wall of water in both directions 4ft, 5ft, 6ft, sometimes 8ft high, and decide to turnt and ride it. 

Thirdly, it pushes me.  I can’t control the ocean I can only harness what is there. If I fight it is doesn’t work with me, if I use what it has, I can benefit and have a great experience.  I of course have to act, paddle hard, prep for the conditions and position myself for the best advantage to ride, but more importantly its the combination of what is there, using what is front of me to have an incredible journey. 

Maybe you get some insight from this, maybe you don’t for me it certainly gives me a refreshing perspective on everything. No wave is the same. No ocean or ocean I surf around the world is the same. Life and business constantly fluctuates and you have to reposition and readjust to create the best possible experience. 

Special thanks to @surfing.surfside for an awesome competition and trip in the DR 

PS: There is a longer slower down version on my YouTube going up check it out and subscribe if you haven’t. 

#surf #surfing #attitude #adrenaline #picoftheday #reels #reelsinstagram #ig #igtravel #travel #lifestyle #business #mindset

When I built the Accelerator Program, it happened by accident. I flew to a client and went to three different cities, shot all this content came home. 

I did a simple post about it and everyone asked for it. 

So I built the package. 

My intention on doing so was to really get the ultimate solution for content creation, marketing, social media, web design all rolled into one package.  To get someone, to get a business - everything they need to win and expand as fast as possible. 

***How it works:
☑ We have a discovery conversation - identify needs, wants, goals
☑ We select the package that makes the most sense
☑ We setup two onboarding calls
☑ I write up the content for you for your review
☑ The team connects to your social platforms
☑ Schedule the film date
☑ I fly out to you - film everything in less than 7 hours
☑ The Content (from date of filming) 40 long form videos, 40 reels/shorts, 400 photos, 45 graphics are delivered

☑ All social platforms rebranded and optimized
☑ Content gets Approved by you (including website)
☑ You keep all RAW Photos, All RAW Footage
☑ Your website is built in your account, which you manage and own
☑ Then we start the 90 Day Program across all social accounts, including advertising campaigns
☑ Weekly meetings with me booked to review performance
☑ Weekly Advertising reports sent every Friday
☑ Website updates and changes as needed
☑ Brand is expanded
Its that simple. 

Send a message now to discuss further and find out pricing options!

I had a recent conversation at an event I was at and we spoke about various different topics. One being the need for change as your business evolves. 

The key take away I got was that things changes, the dynamic changes, the vision expands and sometimes systems that were in place, people that were there change. And that is ok.  I had this weird drilled in thought that you shouldn’t talk about that, or admit you were going through change. That was blown away as the conversation continued. 

Reaching new levels presents new problems, which in turn require adaptability to what you encounter. Being willing to experience change and have those tough conversations with people and do those uncomfortable actions are necessary. It’s part of the process and part of the journey. 

Being real in the conversation, gave me such a huge understanding that what I felt and was experiencing was normal. Sometimes just being real with another heavy hitter is enough to affirm what you’re doing and where you’re going, and to inspire further steps to the main goal.

Im all about scaling now.  And what I keep discovering from my agency is that the internal process and the way things are setup has to align with what I want to take in. Alot of entrepreneurs back off because they cant handle new growth, I don’t have this issue. 

Why because I looked honestly at my people, honestly at my process and tweaked it until it could handle anything that I throw at it.  My friend and I call this the high speed wobbles, but with the right systems the right processes you can sustain scale and growth. In a marketing agency, this is critical because you can overwhelm the system easily with incoming communication and deliverables. 

If you’re not thinking with a solution for everything, a solution that attacks everything head on, the system can collapse in on itself.

Don’t retract, build better systems and build better people.

#entrepreneurs #marketing #communication

I owe a great deal to him because he told, that camera of yours, the lens of yours is the focus point to your problem. It is the solution, your craft and your skill.  I never forgot that conversation, I was living in New Mexico at that time. I had always loved cameras and filming since I was young, it was that moment that I decided that I would make a lifestyle and career out of it.  Having traveled all across the US, built a thriving business in content creation, advertising and marketing, Im so happy that I committed to that one thing I was great at, and expanded upon it.
